Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
popoe is a FRAMEWORK that orchestrates external models and toolkits. The Apache-2.0
license above covers popoe's own code only. Each upstream component keeps its own
license, which you must comply with when you install and use it. popoe does NOT
vendor these; they are optional/external dependencies.

- DINOv2 (visual features)         — Apache-2.0    — github.com/facebookresearch/dinov2
- SAM 2 (segmentation)             — Apache-2.0    — github.com/facebookresearch/sam2
- GeDi (geometric descriptor)      — see upstream  — github.com/fabiopoiesi/gedi  (POPOE_GEDI_PATH)
- dGeDi (distilled GeDi, optional) — see upstream  — github.com/tev-fbk/dGeDi
- CNOS (segmentation proposals)    — see upstream  — github.com/nv-nguyen/cnos
- FreeZe / FreeZeV2 (method this reference implementation reproduces)
                                   — see upstream  — the FreeZe papers/repos
- BOP toolkit (evaluation)         — MIT-style     — github.com/thodan/bop_toolkit  (POPOE_BOP_TOOLKIT)
- nvdiffrast (rendering, optional) — NVIDIA Source Code License — github.com/NVlabs/nvdiffrast

Before redistributing or using popoe with these components, verify each upstream
license (some carry non-commercial or research-only terms). This NOTICE is a
pointer, not legal advice.
